                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d94">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/451: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-10T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 10, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 10—8:15
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>361. Foreign Office informed me this morning that subsequent to handing me the
                    memorandum contained in my 359, August 9, 7 p.m., a copy was given the Japanese
                    Chargé d’Affaires. The French and Italian Governments will be informed next week
                    that the United States and Japanese Governments have received these copies.</p>
                <p>Foreign Office particularly asked that the information contained in my telegram
                    359, August 9, 7 p.m., and the contents of the memorandum be regarded as
                    strictly confidential as between Governments, laying emphasis on the desire that
                    none of the contents would reach the press.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
